<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>The mayor of Rochester, New York, has requested a federal investigation into the death of Daniel Prude, a black man who was suffocated by police officers in the street back in March. </p>

<p>Mayor Lovely Warren disclosed her request for a federal probe on Monday and ordered Rochester Police Chief La'Ron Singletary to step down immediately, according to News8.  </p>

<p>The announcements came after Rochester endured more than a week of protests over the death of 41-year-old Prude, who died several days after being restrained by police March 23. </p>

<p>This is a developing story. </p>

<p>Rochester Mayor Lovely Warren (left) on Monday called for a federal investigation into the death of Daniel Prude (right) who was suffocated by police officers in the street back in March </p>

<p>Warren also ordered Police Chief La'Ron Singletary (pictured) to step down immediately </p>
